name: UpperGIDiseases
title: Upper GI Diseases
description: SNOMED CT intensional (rule-based) value set for defining upper GI disease diagnoses, available for a range of potential uses including problem-oriented views of relevant clinical information, clinical decision support rules, electronic patient registries, and data analytics.
purpose: (Clinical Focus: Broad group of diagnosis concepts for diseases and disorders of the upper gastrointestinal tract (esophagus and stomach).),(Data Element Scope: Employs SNOMED CT concept hierarchies primarily in the Disorder (Clinical finding) branch, though some can be in the Situation with Explicit Context branch or the Procedure branch.),(Inclusion Criteria: Includes benign disorders of the esophagus and stomach, such as esophagitis, esophageal spasm, gastritis, and peptic ulcer disease, among others. Also includes history of these disorders.),(Exclusion Criteria: Does not include cancers of the esophagus and stomach by themselves.)
